<item>
            <title>[LU-11865] Use loopback address instead of 0 for loopback NID</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11865</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the NID for loopback shows as &quot;0@lo&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
# lnetctl net show
net:
    - net type: lo
      local NI(s):
        - nid: 0@lo
          status: up
          interfaces:
              0: lo

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be better if the&#160; loopback IP address is used instead of 0 in loopback NID.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
